<TEXT>
to his lawyer hes johnny to the media the 
dapper don to authorities the gambino crime family boss 
call him what you like but john joseph gotti jr has captured 
the public imagination like no gangster since capone 
his acquittal friday of conspiracy and assault in the shooting 
of a union official only added to his growing aura of 
invincibility which started when predecessor paul castellano was 
gunned down in december 1985 
since that slaying gottis beaten a pair of government cases 
while allegedly running the nations most powerful mob 
organization and he has become americas bestknown crime figure 
his penchant for 1800 suits silk shirts and diamond pinkie 
rings have contributed to his image as a throwback to the mobsters 
of old 
despite continual fbi surveillance gotti keeps a high profile 
making daily trips to hangouts like the bergin hunt and fish club 
in the borough of queens and the ravenite social club in manhattan 
he dines out frequently and enjoys italian food as his stocky 
5foot10 build attests 
phone taps have revealed gotti to be hottempered with a taste 
for gambling many of his friends and reputed crime associates date 
to his childhood one of them is actor ray sharkey who portrayed 
mob boss sonny steelgrave on the television show wiseguy 
sharkey and gotti grew up in the same brooklyn neighborhood 
they ate together at a restaurant recently after they hugged and 
kissed in court 
what do you think defense lawyer bruce cutler is my only 
friend gotti told reporters who expressed surprise 
gotti who turns 50 in october lives with his wife of 29 years 
victoria all agree he is a devoted family man though law 
enforcement officials say the family to whom he is devoted is the 
gambino organization 
in 1979 gotti suffered a family tragedy the death of his 
12yearold son frank who was riding a motorbike when he was 
struck by a neighbors car the accident was a tragedy for the 
neighbor too he disappeared four months later and has never been 
found 
authorities say another death no accident vaulted gotti into 
the position of capo di tutti capi the bold executions of 
castellano and bodyguard thomas bilotti outside a manhattan steak 
house on dec 16 1985 
no one has ever been charged with his murder but within days of 
the castellano hit police detectives reported seeing 100 organized 
crime figures paying their respects to gotti 
since then his lifestyle has been consistent with the 
stereotypical image of a mafia don he travels in a black stretch 
mercedes and he wears his expensive suits with matching ties and 
handkerchiefs 
yet gotti claims he is a salesman for the arc plumbing amp heating 
co of queens his attorney cutler says gotti is nothing more 
than an upfront guy who doesnt fit into their preconceptions of a 
ninetofiver 
so he didnt go to harvard so he gambled a little that makes 
him a mob leader asked cutler the government is very very 
resentful of his popularity jealous of him 
there is no questioning gottis popularity in his queens 
neighborhood he returned like a conquering hero after his 
acquittal on racketeering charges in 1987 during the carpenters 
union assault trial local merchants strung a banner across 101st 
street wishing him luck 
every year he funds a fourth of july street party in queens 
hordes of police have tried to stop the fireworks there to no 
avail 
gotti reputedly earned his mob stripes with the 1973 slaying of 
james mcbratney in a staten island bar he did two years in jail 
for the slaying after pleading guilty to attempted manslaughter in 
a pleabargaining agreement 
during the 1960s gotti was jailed twice one year for grand 
larceny and 3 years for hijacking 
but lately his legal luck has changed his only convictions in 
the past five years are traffic violations with cutlers help he 
beat a massive federal racketeering and conspiracy case 
the dapper don also beat an assault charge when the alleged 
victim after finding out who gotti was testified he was unable 
to identify his attackers i forgotti headlined the new york 
post after the 1986 trial 
the victories apparently convinced gotti he had become the 
teflon don untouchable by the authorities gotti never even 
flinched when dozens of law enforcement officers swooped down to 
arrest him last year for the union shooting 
an unflustered gotti surveyed the situation and said 
threetoone odds i beat this 
once again he was right 
</TEXT>
