<TEXT>
fifteen years after the communist 
takeover the ao dai a traditional costume is making a comeback 
in vietnamese schools the vietnam news agency reported 
increasing numbers of schoolgirls in ho chi minh city have been 
wearing the long flowing white garment which was the traditional 
school uniform until 1975 the agency reported 
until that year ho chi minh city formerly saigon was the 
capital of the usbacked government of south vietnam 
a modified version of the ao dai has reappeared as a school 
uniform for girls since last year according to the report 
monitored in bangkok 
the readoption of the ao dai in schools comes under an effort 
by authorities in ho chi minh city to restore and develop national 
identity the report said 
the agency quoted a 17yearold student duong thi thanh thanh 
as saying she saw in the white robe the symbol of both the 
physical beauty and the finest virtues of vietnamese women 
