<TEXT>
a moderately strong earthquake hit coastal china 
north of shanghai early today but there were no immediate reports 
of damage or injuries the official xinhua news agency said 
the quake measuring 51 on the richter scale was centered east 
of changshu city in jiangsu province about 56 miles northwest of 
shanghai 
it was felt in shanghai the provincial capital of nanjing and 
the cities of wuxi and nantong 
china is one of the worlds most quakeprone lands among recent 
tremors three were killed in november when the southwest province 
of sichuan was hit by quakes measuring up to 54 on the richter 
scale and at least 29 died in a series of heavy tremors 
registering up to 61 in northern chinas shanxi province in 
october 
the richter scale gauges the energy released by an earthquake 
measured by the ground motion recorded on a seismograph a quake 
measuring 5 can cause considerable damage in a populated area one 
measuring 6 can cause severe damage 
</TEXT>
