a responsibility to protect poindexters rights but his lawyers 
also said reagan retains the right to invoke executive privilege to 
specific questions during the deposition 
indicating they expect bush administration representatives to be 
permitted to attend the deposition reagans lawyers said they will 
defer to the incumbent president regarding issues of executive 
privilege on national security or foreign affairs 
the former national security adviser is charged with conspiracy 
two counts of obstructing congress and two counts of making false 
statements 
greene will attend the deposition to rule on disputes claiming 
executive privilege to specific questions could result in halting 
the deposition in midstream and taking the matter through court 
appeals or more likely the deposition would continue while the 
specific questions at issue remain unanswered pending appeals 
the videotape deposition format will provide an appropriate 
mechanism to protect sensitive classified national security 
information and confidential deliberations reagans lawyers said 
the edited videotape would be shown at poindexters trial 
