to the whales last week vessels should keep at least 100 yards 
from the whales and aircraft must fly at a minimum altitude of 
1000 feet while within a 100yard radius of the whales he said 
i dont want to scare people or blindside them he said 
were just trying to get people to enjoy the whales but to give 
them a little bit of room 
if you were out in south dakota and saw a buffalo in the 
middle of a field you wouldnt drive your car out in the middle of 
it to see the animal he said but thats what some people are 
doing out in the water with the whales 
the gray whales which are protected under the marine mammal 
protection act hug the southern california coast on their journey 
from alaska to their breeding grounds off baja california 
