german reunification 
foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze told a news conference 
in moscow before kohls arrival that one of the key issues to be 
discussed was the need for a german guarantee on stable borders 
he also expressed support for a neutral demilitarized 
germany 
the chancellor has argued that soviet security interests would 
not be threatened if the two german states merged into a country of 
80 million people in the heart of europe 
after returning from the weekend talks in moscow kohl will meet 
in bonn with east german premier hans modrow see french president 
