council president was apparently put off with iliescu a strong 
favorite 
this first meeting which was quite heated led to consensus 
and a final list of council members iliescu said at the end of 
the 7hour session 
an earlier decision to increase the council to 241 members was 
expanded to give even greater representation 
the assembly building is being used for the first time since the 
uprising against ceausescu who was overthrown dec 22 and executed 
three days later the council agreed to meet again tuesday 
the first four hours of debate friday centered on whether nine 
new parties registered in the last week should be given seats and 
on questions regarding the seating of ethnic groups 
in the expanded council 114 seats went to 38 parties 27 seats 
to nine organizations representing ethnic minorities three seats 
will be filled by former political prisoners and 114 seats go to 
prominent romanians from all walks of life who were part of the 
national salvation front the president is to fill the remaining 
seat 
before fridays session the legality of the decree creating the 
council was challenged by the national peasants party which 
opposed granting a large number of seats to former national front 
members it later dropped its challenge 
in another development a colonel awaiting trial on charges of 
complicity in genocide during the revolution committed suicide by 
hanging himself with his belt in a jail cell in timosoara the 
daily romania libera reported friday 
before his suicide col petre moraru told journalists of 
details of a clandestine operation to transfer the bodies of people 
killed in the first days of the revolt from timisoara to bucharest 
to be cremated 
also friday silviu brucan who resigned from the front 
leadership last month confirmed that some of ceausescus hated 
securitate secret police remained at large 
</TEXT>
