getting a place of his own and a job as a computer operator 
the accusations against ritter he added are unimportant the 
philosophy behind what father ritter has done is whats important 
why dont they talk about the good things hes done 
complained nina spear 19 who came to covenant house 2 months ago 
after living on the street for 2 years she left her home on 
staten island because she said her life was messed up drugs 
family 
at covenant house she said they teach us discipline 
selfrespect respect for others instead of sleeping on the 
subway you sleep in a bed 
andrew escalet 21 who has been at covenant house for more than 
a year and hopes to be on his own by may said i dont feel any 
disappointment i feel its irrelevant theres people that do so 
much worse in this world 
escalets family kicked him out of his house in the bronx two 
years ago i stayed with friends he recalled several times 
i stayed out in the parks and slept in a box got to a time when i 
needed some sort of rescue it wasnt nobody else but covenant 
house 
