<TEXT>
hundreds of procuban rebels ambushed a police 
post in a remote jungle town early saturday and fired on it for 
hours trapping 19 officers inside and killing two authorities 
said 
the report said three rebels of the tupac amaru revolutionary 
movement also died in the battle 
according to the report a column of 200 rebels surrounded the 
police post in the town of picota 470 miles north of lima before 
dawn saturday 
while some rebels kept the officers trapped officers inside 
others burned banks and government offices in the town police 
said two officers died and five were wounded 
an interior ministry spokesman said police and army 
reinforcements left saturday morning for the zone and all roads to 
picota had been closed 
the tupac army began fighting perus elected governments in 1984 
and is the secondlargest insurgent group operating in the country 
the stronger shining path a maoist group launched its insurgency 
in 1980 
police friday reported nine deaths that were blamed on the 
shining path last week 
