<TEXT>
less than a year after helping his first 
wife take her own life so she would not die a slow painful death 
from cancer derek humphry married again 
with his new wife ann he founded the hemlock society an 
organization that became a leader in the righttodie movement 
but after ann w humphry was diagnosed with breast cancer last 
year the couple became embroiled in a bitter divorce that has left 
mrs humphry accusing her estranged husband of abandoning the 
societys most basic principles as well as abusing his leadership 
its a tragic case of a lot of dirty linen being washed in 
public said william batt a director of the national 
organization and president of the societys upstate new york 
chapter 
last month the societys board of directors restructured the 
organization it voted both humphrys off the board appointed derek 
humphry executive director and placed ann humphry on sick leave 
the board expressed full confidence in derek humphry board 
member faye girsh of san diego said its his vision 
the moves were long overdue board members said it was really 
a momandpop organization board member john westover of tucson 
ariz said last week it had really outgrown the situation 
in fact the board would like someone else to take over 
administrative duties so that derek humphry can devote himself to 
developing policy and spreading the societys message westover said 
the intertwined story of derek and ann humphry and the hemlock 
society began when they were married 13 years ago in england he 
was a british journalist she was an american academic 
in 1978 they moved to los angeles where they founded the 
hemlock society in 1980 to crusade for the right to choose death 
as humphrys first wife jean had done 
the humphrys moved hemlock in 1988 to eugene ore where the 
national organization employs 13 people and counts 53 chapters 
across the united states 
ann humphry bought a 50acre farm in monroe 20 miles north of 
eugene where the couple lived until last october three weeks 
after she was diagnosed with breast cancer derek humphry went on a 
speaking tour in new mexico and never came home again 
she wouldnt let me have anything to do with her cancer 
said humphry 59 she wouldnt let me come to the hospital she 
wouldnt tell me the details she said you stay out of it 
he said his wife finally changed her mind but began to taunt 
him about his previous wife 
would i do the same for her did i love her as much as my 
first wife things were said that i could not bear the 
marriage just broke to pieces in my eyes and i left her 
it was a bad marriage for four or five years he said the 
cancer just cracked it open the cancer just finished it off 
ann humphry acknowledged that the couple had been seeing 
marriage counselors 
she said she had been growing more distant from both her husband 
and the hemlock society in recent years and the cancer was the 
final straw 
i think it was a terrible blow to him she said he said 
i cannot live with this misery any longer i dont choose to live 
through what i lived through once he added that if i were dying 
he would make certain that i would be looked after 
derek humphry said the point was she was not dying that the 
lump had been removed from her breast in time and her physician 
gave her a 75 percent chance of recovery 
in addition ann humphry said she believed her husband has hurt 
the righttodie movement 
