a medical report said 
michele died within 45 minutes after the ventilator was shut 
off said tynan professor of pediatric cardiology at the hospital 
he died in his parents arms we were doing our best to ensure 
he did not have any unnecessary suffering tynan told a news 
conference 
the exact cause of death was not given 
he said the decision to turn off the ventilator which assisted 
the childs breathing was made by medical staff and the parents 
ann and bernard vermilio 
doctors said the baby suffered from a rare defect called 
critical aortic stenosis a blockage of the aortic valve in which 
blood cannot be pumped at the right pressure heart failure can 
result 
lindsay allan the doctor in charge of the fetal cardiology 
unit said most fetuses with the defect die in the womb and the few 
who survive birth do not live more than a day 
she said the two operations on the fetus involved inserting a 
catheter a slender tube down a hollow needle directly into the 
chest wall and heart 
once in place the tiny plastic balloon measuring 11 of an 
inch was inflated with a saline solution to open the heart valve 
ms allan said 
the mother received a local anesthetic and was awake during both 
operations 
there was no indication that the fetus felt anything said 
darryl maxwell director of the hospitals fetal medicine unit who 
monitored the surgery with an ultrasonic scanner 
</TEXT>
