<TEXT>
west german chancellor helmut kohl said saturday 
that soviet president mikhail s gorbachev promised to respect 
german reunification and he declared it a very good day for 
germany 
kohl and foreign minister hansdietrich genscher also disclosed 
that they expect a reunification plan with agreement of the four 
victorious world war ii allies to be ready this year to present to 
a paneuropean summit meeting 
at a news conference following 2hours of talks with gorbachev 
kohl gave a glowing assessment of relations with the soviet union 
and the kremlins attitude toward the accelerating developments 
between east and west germany 
kohl said he acknowledged in his talk with gorbachev that de 
facto reunification is occurring faster than anyone expected and 
said the two germanies along with the allies must work out a 
program for controlling it 
gorbachev agreed that the decision on reunification is the 
sole right of the german people including the time frame and the 
method kohl said 
the official soviet news agency tass carried a report on the 
gorbachevkohl meeting that supported kohls assessment 
kohl said the world war ii allies the united states britain 
france and the soviet union should be consulted in reunification 
planning 
this should happen between the two german governments but 
not behind the backs of the four powers the chancellor said 
at the end of this year there would be an opportunity within a 
summitlevel european conference to discuss and announce these 
results kohl said the soviets had previously suggested such a 
meeting 
general secretary gorbachev told me unequivocally that the 
soviet union will respect the decision of germans to live in one 
state kohl said this is a very good day for germany and a 
happy day for me personally 
kohl and soviet foreign ministry spokesman gennady i gerasimov 
indicated that a clear promise to respect the current boundaries 
outlining east germany and west germany also would be contained in 
a reunification plan 
kohl was received in the kremlin for an evening of negotiations 
with gorbachev who is trying to cut soviet losses from the 
democratic revolution that has drawn east germany away from the 
warsaw pact 
gorbachevs acknowledgment nearly two weeks ago that german 
unification was inevitable set off a chain reaction of events that 
have stepped up the movement toward a single germany 
tass commented in a report on the kohlgorbachev meeting that a 
new political situation has evolved in central europe and the two 
german states determine its nature in many respects 
the soviets face potentially major losses in military and 
economic cooperation if east germany joins with the rich west 
german nation now part of the nato alliance 
kohl on a twoweek diplomatic sweep to forge a unity plan 
acceptable to both east and west brought with him an offer of 132 
million in aid for soviet food purchases apparently to demonstrate 
that germany will help restore the economic losses from redirected 
east german trade 
east germany has suffered a severe economic decline in recent 
months as an exodus to west germany increasingly claims its best 
workers and precludes independent efforts at recovery 
as many as 3000 east germans flee the uncertainty in their 
homeland each day and some west german officials fear imminent 
collapse 
soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze told reporters 
before the west german officials arrived that the kremlin sought 
assurances that a reunited germany would recognize current borders 
and never rise as a threat to its european neighbors 
both west germany and east germany are bound by treaties to 
respect the current borders of europe but a united germany is not 
committed to those terms 
conservatives in west germany have suggested that reunification 
should be sought within the 1937 borders which include areas in 
the soviet union as well as nearly a third of presentday poland 
shevardnadze called the border issue the most relevant issue 
to be resolved in the reunification process shevardnadze and 
genscher held their own talks before joining gorbachev and kohl 
the soviets also have pressed for a neutral germany in the event 
the two states are united a condition rejected by bonn as well as 
nato 
while soviet approval and that of the other victor powers would 
be needed to transfer control of berlin to a united germany the 
kremlin has little clout in determining the political shape of the 
reunited state 
last years prodemocracy uprisings throughout eastern europe 
have weakened the economic and defense bonds with the oncedominant 
soviet union and the potential loss of east germany would deal the 
kremlin its most harmful blow 
twothirds of the soviets 575000 europeanbased troops are 
deployed in east germany which is also the most important allied 
trading partner for the economically troubled soviets 
kohl returns to bonn for meetings with east german premier hans 
modrow on tuesday and wednesday when the west germans plans for 
economic integration with east germany will again be the primary 
topic of discussion 
kohl will see french president francois mitterrand after his 
talks with modrow then travel to camp david to meet with president 
bush 
east germans on march 18 vote in their firstever free 
elections and kohl has said he will negotiate the details of 
reunification only with the new elected leadership 
