just crashed into the water 
six firefighters and two police officers were treated at the 
scene for exposure apuzzo said 
rescue efforts were aided by relatively calm water although the 
national weather service said water temperatures were likely in the 
low 40s helicopters and an assortment of boats were brought in to 
pull people from the water 
the helicopter was owned by island helicopter corp deputy 
police chief ron johnson said a woman who answered the telephone 
at island helicopters office confirmed that the copter was one of 
islands and said it had been taking off for a sightseeing trip 
around manhattan when it crashed 
the national transportation safety board was investigating the 
crash said kathleen bergen a spokeswoman for the federal aviation 
administration she said the faa was speaking for the ntsb under a 
local agreement 
police said the critically injured boy was from long island and 
his father who also was on the helicopter lived in new jersey 
the other two passengers on the helicopter were visitors from 
france and the pilot lives on long island resident police said 
it was the third time in the last five years that an island 
helicopter coming into the east side helipad had gone into the 
river a may 2 1988 crash of another sightseeing helicopter 
killed a japanese businessman three years earlier a west german 
man died when a copter with eight people aboard went down 
the accident occurred just two blocks from a helipad on the east 
river where sightseeing copters and a shuttle to kennedy 
international airport are based 
