<TEXT>
the chief executive of the american medical 
association resigned a year before he planned to retire amid 
revelations about moneylosing deals involving ama investments and 
two top staff members 
i am convinced that the ama should focus on the future now and 
not wait until i go as planned dr james h sammons said in a 
news release the ama issued saturday 
sammons 62 who is credited with guiding the association 
through hard financial times over 15 years had his fiscal 
discretion curtailed two months ago by ama trustees who praised 
him on his departure 
the board of trustees said at its interim annual meeting in 
honolulu that sammons had failed to follow routine fiscal policies 
in approving deals between himself and two staff members 
in one deal approved by sammons in 1987 the ama used 
pensionfund investments to reimburse one of the staffers 353000 
for his losses in the stock market crash 
the officer resigned and has since paid back the money sammons 
turned in his resignation friday the ama statement said 
in another deal approved by sammons in 1989 the ama lost 
65000 in a foreclosure settlement on a 267710 loan it had given 
one of sammons assistants to buy a condominium 
the deals were brought to light last fall by the sun times of 
chicago which published more details last week 
the newspaper reported that the ama lost 45000 in the 1984 
purchase of sammons suburban home and sale of the home a year 
later 
the newspaper also described a similar deal in 1980 in which the 
ama bought a home owned by sammons top deputy and later sold it at 
a loss of 23000 
the washington state medical association subsequently called for 
sammons to step aside during an investigation of ama finances 
which the board initiated in october 
the illinois state medical society made an official call for 
such a probe and two other ama affiliates asked that sammons 
powers be limited 
ama trustee dr joseph painter said sammons increased the amas 
assets from 25 million to 193 million helped increase membership 
by 100000 to more than 270000 and expansion the associations 
activities in such areas as medical publishing education science 
and disease prevention 
the board saturday named dr james s todd acting executive vice 
president to replace sammons todd a former chairman of the ama 
board has been the organizations senior deputy vice president for 
five years 
</TEXT>
