<TEXT>
a man who didnt remember his past when 
found wandering in a parking lot by police four month ago was 
identified saturday by people who said they were kin 
they found him through a television news report 
the man was identified by the people as melvin wolf a 
53yearold former serviceman who had been living with his sister 
in texas until august 
theres no doubt that hes melvin wolf said the sister 
donna caskey of angleton texas after the meeting the doctor 
said his memory will probably come back gradually 
in october the man was found with no identification and became 
known as john doe a therapist put him through hypnosis which 
helped him remember pieces of his past including a us army 
serial number the number belongs to melvin wolf 
mrs caskey her husband charlie and their son james met the 
man and his therapist rick selig at the topeka psychiatric clinic 
she and other relatives had talked to him by telephone on friday 
without spurring any recollections of his past and saturdays 
meeting again left him unable to remember 
they called him melvin and said dont you remember me 
they showed him various pictures and other family mementoes and 
although wolf said a few things seemed familiar he was still 
unable to recall who he was 
its a little confusing to him said james caskey 30 he 
said theres no doubt theres some connection with all the pictures 
and the things weve been telling him but he doesnt know us 
saturdays reunion came after other relatives in wisconsin had 
seen a story about him 
selig had developed information that there might be a wisconsin 
connection and reporter russ ptacek of topekas wibwtv called tv 
in that state on thursday to encourage them to use a story he had 
done about the case 
ptacek said that minutes after his story was aired on wititv in 
milwaukee thursday night two people living in wisconsin 
independently called the station and said they were relatives 
ptacek then called selig and police to tell them of the 
developments topeka police said saturday they were still 
investigating the case they were still waiting on a fingerprint 
check 
in recent sessions selig had doe draw things under hypnosis 
including a detailed sketch of what appeared to be a map 
it had no meaning to anyone until saturday when mrs caskey 
looked at it and said it was the layout of the farm in wisconsin 
where she said they grew up 
mrs caskey said that wolf had lived with her and her family in 
angleton where she said he owned an electronics repair store she 
said he left home last aug 20 on a business trip to washington 
dc and never returned 
selig a clinical social worker said the man was diagnosed as 
suffering from psychogenic amnesia a total memory loss that he 
said can result from some extraordinarily stressful event 
</TEXT>
