nasas galileo spacecraft snapped 
photographs of venus today after zooming around the planet in a 
celestial billiard shot that sent the robot explorer toward its 
1995 encounter with jupiter 
we have clearly achieved the sole objective of going to venus 
a trajectory that will help us ultimately reach jupiter said 
bill oneil galileo science and mission design manager at nasas 
jet propulsion laboratory all systems have been operating 
perfectly 
the 28ton spacecraft made its closest approach to venus at 
959 pm pst friday passing 10028 miles above the furnacelike 
surface of the second planet from the sun oneil said 
galileos camera snapped pictures of the planet to study wind 
and cloud patterns and search for lightning that might indicate the 
presence of volcanoes erupting beneath the clouds 
